@node Source playback
@section Source playback

@samp{C-c SPC} (@samp{eve-play}) or @samp{SPC} / @samp{RET} (@samp{eve-play-segment}) plays the
source media from the current segment to the end of the clip.  All segments
from the same source file are tracked, so the playback highlight follows even
across segments.

Playback position maps directly to the original recording timestamps.

@node Rendered playback
@section Rendered playback

@samp{C-u C-c SPC} (@samp{eve-play} with prefix) or @samp{C-c C-p} (@samp{eve-play-rendered})
plays the compiled output file.  If the output is missing or older than the
manifest, eve compiles it first.

Progress is tracked using the post-edit rendered timeline; deleted content is
skipped in the position calculation.

@node Playback tracking and segment highlighting
@section Playback tracking and segment highlighting

Eve integrates with mpv via its JSON IPC socket.  The currently-playing
segment is highlighted with a vivid amber overlay (@samp{eve-playback-face}),
distinct from both the focus highlight and the region.

@node Controls
@section Controls

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Key
@tab Action
@item @samp{SPC} (during playback)
@tab Pause / resume.
@item Move point to a segment
@tab Seek mpv to that segment's start time.
@item @samp{C-c k} / @samp{M-x eve-stop-playback}
@tab Stop playback and restore keybindings.
@item @samp{<left>}
@tab Seek backward @samp{eve-seek-short-seconds} (default 5s).
@item @samp{<right>}
@tab Seek forward @samp{eve-seek-short-seconds} (default 5s).
@item @samp{S-<left>}
@tab Seek backward @samp{eve-seek-long-backward-seconds} (default 30s).
@item @samp{S-<right>}
@tab Seek forward @samp{eve-seek-long-forward-seconds} (default 10s).
@end multitable

Stopping playback restores all keybindings to their normal state.

@node Video layout
@section Video layout

Set @samp{eve-video-layout} to @samp{t} to arrange the screen for editing: Emacs takes
the bottom portion of the display and mpv sits directly above it —
borderless, always-on-top, with automatic letterboxing.

@lisp
(setq eve-video-layout t)

;; Fraction of screen height for the video window (default 0.6 = 60%)
(setq eve-video-layout-ratio 0.6)
@end lisp

The layout activates on the first play command and the original frame geometry
is restored when playback stops.  Skipped when Emacs is in macOS native
fullscreen.

