@node Timestamp ruler
@section Timestamp ruler

@samp{eve-ruler-mode} (active by default) displays @samp{[hh:mm:ss]} markers in the
right margin.  Each marker is placed next to the segment that @emph{reaches} that
milestone in the rendered video — deleted content is excluded from the running
total.

The total rendered duration appears in the mode line.

@lisp
;; Change the milestone interval (default 30 seconds)
(setq eve-ruler-interval 60.0)
@end lisp

Toggle the ruler with @samp{C-c C-l} (@samp{eve-ruler-mode}).

@node Hiding deleted segments
@section Hiding deleted segments

@samp{C-c C-h} (@samp{eve-hide-deleted-mode}) toggles visibility of deleted words and
segments.  When active (the default), deleted content is hidden and the
transcript reads as it will render.  When inactive, deleted content appears
with a strikethrough face.

@node Word-level display
@section Word-level display

@samp{C-c C-w} (@samp{eve-toggle-words}) shows or hides per-word timing annotations
under each segment.  Useful when inspecting or adjusting precise cut points.

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Variable
@tab Default
@tab Description
@item @samp{eve-ruler-interval}
@tab @samp{30.0}
@tab Seconds between ruler markers.
@item @samp{eve-show-words-by-default}
@tab @samp{nil}
@tab Show word timings on buffer open.
@item @samp{eve-validation-on-save}
@tab @samp{t}
@tab Validate manifest on every save.
@item @samp{eve-validation-time-tolerance}
@tab @samp{0.1}
@tab Timing slack tolerated during validation (seconds).
@end multitable

